basicLogLimit.name: basicLogLimit
basicLogLimit.description: Maximum allowed number of kilobytes for recording events. Corresponds directly to MANAGER LOG FILE SIZE and the value labeled 'Log File Size:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicActiveLimit.name: basicActiveLimit
basicActiveLimit.description: Maximum allowed number of simultaneous service dialogs. Corresponds directly to MANAGER SIMULTANEOUS and the value labeled 'Maximum simultaneous requests:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

basicActiveNumber.name: basicActiveNumber
basicActiveNumber.description: Number of active service dialogs. Corresponds indirectly to the list of active clients in the MANAGER STATUS display.

basicClientNumber.name: basicClientNumber
basicClientNumber.description: Number of defined clients. Corresponds indirectly to the list of defined clients in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

basicOffersSent.name: basicOffersSent
basicOffersSent.description: Total number of service offers sent in response to client requests. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Total service offers sent:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

basicEventTotal.name: basicEventTotal
basicEventTotal.description: Total number of events that have been written to the event log since it was last purged. This may be less than the number currently in the log. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Total Messages Logged:' in the MANAGER EVENTS display.

basicEventPurge.name: basicEventPurge
basicEventPurge.description: Control to cause emptying the event log. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' causes the event log to immediately become empty. Corresponds directly to the PURGE MANAGER LOG FILE command.

activeTable.name: activeTable
activeTable.description: A list of active client dialog entries. The number of entries is given by basicActiveNumber.

activeEntry.name: activeEntry
activeEntry.description: Parameter values for an active client dialog entry.

activeIdentificationType.name: activeIdentificationType
activeIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in activeIdentification. Corresponds indirectly to the value labeled 'EthernetAddress' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeIdentification.name: activeIdentification
activeIdentification.description: Identification of the active partner. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'EthernetAddress' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeFunction.name: activeFunction
activeFunction.description: The function the server is performing with the partner. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Function' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeSoftwareVersionType.name: activeSoftwareVersionType
activeSoftwareVersionType.description: If activeFunction is 'load', the software version being sent to the client, otherwise 'notApplicable'. Corresponds to the letter in the software version labeled 'Version' in the MANAGER STATUS display. alpha 'A': alpha test beta 'B': beta test production null: normal, production software special 'S': special, custom software

activeSoftwareVersion.name: activeSoftwareVersion
activeSoftwareVersion.description: If activeFunction is 'load', the 4-byte software version being sent to the client, otherwise zero length. In order, the octets contain major version, minor version, ECO, and pre-release number. Corresponds to the numbers in the software version labeled 'Version' in the MANAGER STATUS display. For example, the version display for activeSoftwareVersionType 'production' and activeSoftwareVersion '2.2.0.0' is 'V2.2'. The version display for activeSoftwareVersionType 'beta' and activeSoftwareVersion '3.1.0.4' is 'V3.1B4'.

activeParameterVersion.name: activeParameterVersion
activeParameterVersion.description: If activeFunction is 'parameterStore', the parameter version being stored by the client, otherwise zero. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Version' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeCurrentSequence.name: activeCurrentSequence
activeCurrentSequence.description: The current dialog sequence number. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Seq' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeBytesRemaining.name: activeBytesRemaining
activeBytesRemaining.description: The number of bytes remaining to be transferred in the dialog. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Left' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeFile.name: activeFile
activeFile.description: The name of the file being used in the dialog. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'File' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

activeStatus.name: activeStatus
activeStatus.description: The final status of the most recent attempt to get an image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Get Status:' in the DEVICE STATUS display.

activeState.name: activeState
activeState.description: The dynamic state of an active attempt to get an image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Get State:' in the DEVICE STATUS display.

clientTable.name: clientTable
clientTable.description: A list of client data base entries. The number of entries is given by basicClientNumber.

clientEntry.name: clientEntry
clientEntry.description: Parameter values for a client data base entry.

clientIdentificationType.name: clientIdentificationType
clientIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in clientIdentification. Corresponds directly to MANAGER NODE, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER LOCAL, and the value labeled 'Ethernet Address' in the MANAGER NODE display or 'Ethernet Address', 'Device', and 'Global Devices' or 'Local Devices' in the MANAGER GLOBAL and LOCAL displays.

clientIdentification.name: clientIdentification
clientIdentification.description: Identification of the client, either a hardware type or an Ethernet address, depending on clientIdentificationType. Corresponds directly to MANAGER NODE, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER LOCAL, and the value labeled 'Ethernet Address' in the MANAGER NODE display or 'Ethernet Address', 'Device', and 'Global Devices' or 'Local Devices' in the MANAGER GLOBAL and LOCAL displays.

clientEntryStatus.name: clientEntryStatus
clientEntryStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds directly to the PURGE LOCAL, PURGE GLOBAL, and PURGE NODE commands. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

clientName.name: clientName
clientName.description: A name that may be used to identify the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Name' in the MANAGER NODE display.

clientLoadFile.name: clientLoadFile
clientLoadFile.description: The file with the client's load image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load File' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

clientDiagnosticFile.name: clientDiagnosticFile
clientDiagnosticFile.description: The file with the client's diagnostic test image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Diag File' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

clientLoadService.name: clientLoadService
clientLoadService.description: Control for allowing load service for the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

clientDumpService.name: clientDumpService
clientDumpService.description: Control for allowing dump service for the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Dump' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

namedTable.name: namedTable
namedTable.description: A list of named client data base entries. The number of entries is given by basicClientNumber.

namedEntry.name: namedEntry
namedEntry.description: Parameter values for a named client data base entry.

namedIdentificationType.name: namedIdentificationType
namedIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in namedIdentification. Corresponds directly to MANAGER NODE, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER LOCAL, and the value labeled 'Ethernet Address' in the MANAGER NODE display or 'Ethernet Address', 'Device', and 'Global Devices' or 'Local Devices' in the MANAGER GLOBAL and LOCAL displays.

namedIdentification.name: namedIdentification
namedIdentification.description: Identification of the client, either a hardware type or an Ethernet address, depending on namedIdentificationType. Corresponds directly to MANAGER NODE, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER LOCAL, and the value labeled 'Ethernet Address' in the MANAGER NODE display or 'Ethernet Address', 'Device', and 'Global Devices' or 'Local Devices' in the MANAGER GLOBAL and LOCAL displays.

namedEntryStatus.name: namedEntryStatus
namedEntryStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds directly to the PURGE LOCAL, PURGE GLOBAL, and PURGE NODE commands. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

namedName.name: namedName
namedName.description: A name that may be used to identify the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Name' in the MANAGER NODE display.

namedLoadFile.name: namedLoadFile
namedLoadFile.description: The file with the client's load image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load File' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

namedDiagnosticFile.name: namedDiagnosticFile
namedDiagnosticFile.description: The file with the client's diagnostic test image. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Diag File' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

namedLoadService.name: namedLoadService
namedLoadService.description: Control for allowing load service for the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

namedDumpService.name: namedDumpService
namedDumpService.description: Control for allowing dump service for the client. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Dump' in the MANAGER LOCAL, MANAGER GLOBAL, and MANAGER NODE displays.

eventTable.name: eventTable
eventTable.description: A list of event entries. The number of entries is given by basicEventNumber.

eventEntry.name: eventEntry
eventEntry.description: Parameter values for a event entry.

eventIndex.name: eventIndex
eventIndex.description: In identification number for an event. The value 1 indicates the oldest event in the file, with subsequent numbers indicating sequential events. The event text for a given number may change as a circular event log wraps over its beginning. Corresponds directly to the relative position of an event in the MANAGER EVENTS display.

eventText.name: eventText
eventText.description: The text of the event, including date, time and other information. Corresponds directly to the individual event text in the MANAGER EVENTS display.

basicDeviceNumber.name: basicDeviceNumber
basicDeviceNumber.description: The system's number of mass-storage devices.

deviceTable.name: deviceTable
deviceTable.description: A list of device entries. The number of entries is given by basicDeviceNumber.

deviceEntry.name: deviceEntry
deviceEntry.description: Parameter values for a device entry.

deviceIndex.name: deviceIndex
deviceIndex.description: In identification number for a device, in the range 1 to basicDeviceNumber

deviceName.name: deviceName
deviceName.description: A name by which the device is known in other displays, such as 'C1' or 'D2'.

deviceDescr.name: deviceDescr
deviceDescr.description: Details of the device type, including, for example, size, manufacturer, Flash versus RAM, and such. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Device Type: in the MANAGER DEVICE STATUS display.

deviceOperation.name: deviceOperation
deviceOperation.description: Current operational state of the device. Corresponds directly the value labeled 'Device Operation:' in the MANAGER DEVICE STATUS display.

deviceFormat.name: deviceFormat
deviceFormat.description: Formatting status of the device. Corresponds directly the presence of one of the value labels under the label 'Device Status:' in the MANAGER DEVICE STATUS display.

deviceProtection.name: deviceProtection
deviceProtection.description: Write-protect status of the device. Corresponds directly the presence of one of the value labels under the label 'Device Status:' in the MANAGER DEVICE STATUS display.

deviceFormatMedium.name: deviceFormatMedium
deviceFormatMedium.description: Control to cause formatting of the medium in the device. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' causes the device to be formatted. Corresponds directly to the FORMAT DEVICE command.

deviceGetFile.name: deviceGetFile
deviceGetFile.description: Control to cause getting a file to the device from a remote host system. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the agent always returns 'ready' for this value. Setting the value to 'ready' has no effect. Setting it to 'execute' causes the get to be attempted. Corresponds directly to the GET DEVICE command. When set to 'execute', the objects deviceGetFileHostIdentificationType, deviceGetFileHostIdentification, and deviceGetFileName must be somewhere in the same set request message.

deviceGetFileHostIdentificationType.name: deviceGetFileHostIdentificationType
deviceGetFileHostIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in deviceIdentification. Corresponds indirectly to ADDRESS in the GET DEVICE command. This object may not be set outside the context of setting deviceGetFile to 'execute'. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the value of this object is 'undefined'.

deviceGetFileHostIdentification.name: deviceGetFileHostIdentification
deviceGetFileHostIdentification.description: Identification of the host to get the file from, with type depending on deviceIdentificationType. Corresponds directly to ADDRESS in the GET DEVICE command. This object may not be set outside the context of setting deviceGetFile to 'execute'. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the value of this object is zero length.

deviceGetFileName.name: deviceGetFileName
deviceGetFileName.description: The name of the file to get. Corresponds directly to LOAD FILE in the GET DEVICE command. This object may not be set outside the context of setting deviceGetFile to 'execute'. In response to a get-request or get-next-request, the value of this object is zero length.

dumpService.name: dumpService
dumpService.description: Control for allowing dump service for any client. Corresponds directly to DUMP and the value labeled 'Dump:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

dumpDrive.name: dumpDrive
dumpDrive.description: Identification number of the disk drive where dumps are stored. Corresponds directly to DUMP DRIVE and the value labeled 'Dump Drive:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

dumpMerit.name: dumpMerit
dumpMerit.description: Relative preference for this dump server over others. Corresponds directly to DUMP MERIT and the value labeled 'Dump Merit:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

dumpSize.name: dumpSize
dumpSize.description: Type of dump file to keep. Corresponds directly to DUMP SIZE and the value labeled 'Dump Size:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

dumpCompleted.name: dumpCompleted
dumpCompleted.description: The number of dumps completed since system initialization. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Dump Operations Completed:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

dumpActive.name: dumpActive
dumpActive.description: The number of dumps in progress. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Currently Dumping:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

dumpFileNumber.name: dumpFileNumber
dumpFileNumber.description: The number of dump files currently stored. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Network dump files' and 'files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

dumpFileTable.name: dumpFileTable
dumpFileTable.description: A list of dump file entries. The number of entries is given by dumpFileNumber.

dumpFileEntry.name: dumpFileEntry
dumpFileEntry.description: Parameter values for a dump file entry.

dumpFileIdentificationType.name: dumpFileIdentificationType
dumpFileIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in dumpFileIdentification. Corresponds indirectly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Network dump files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

dumpFileIdentification.name: dumpFileIdentification
dumpFileIdentification.description: Identification of the dump file, an Ethernet address, as indicated by dumpFileIdentificationType. Corresponds indirectly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Network dump files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

dumpFileEntryStatus.name: dumpFileEntryStatus
dumpFileEntryStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds indirectly to the PURGE MANAGER DUMP FILES command. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

dumpFileCreation.name: dumpFileCreation
dumpFileCreation.description: The time the dump file was created. Corresponds directly to a date and time in the section labeled 'Network dump files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

dumpFileSize.name: dumpFileSize
dumpFileSize.description: The number of bytes stored in the dump file. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'bytes' in the section labeled 'Network dump files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadService.name: loadService
loadService.description: Control for allowing load service for any client. Corresponds directly to LOAD and the value labeled 'Load:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

loadMerit.name: loadMerit
loadMerit.description: Relative preference for this load server over others. Corresponds directly to LOAD MERIT and the value labeled 'Load Merit:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

loadCompleted.name: loadCompleted
loadCompleted.description: The number of loads completed since system initialization. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load Operations Completed:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

loadActive.name: loadActive
loadActive.description: The number of loads in progress. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Currently Loading:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

loadFileNumber.name: loadFileNumber
loadFileNumber.description: The number of load files currently stored. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Load image files' and 'files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadFileTable.name: loadFileTable
loadFileTable.description: A list of load file entries. The number of entries is given by loadFileNumber.

loadFileEntry.name: loadFileEntry
loadFileEntry.description: Parameter values for a load file entry.

loadFileName.name: loadFileName
loadFileName.description: The name of a load file. Corresponds directly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadFileCreation.name: loadFileCreation
loadFileCreation.description: The time the load file was created. Corresponds directly to a date and time in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadFileSize.name: loadFileSize
loadFileSize.description: The number of bytes stored in the load file. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'bytes' in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

loadFileSoftwareVersionType.name: loadFileSoftwareVersionType
loadFileSoftwareVersionType.description: The software version type of the image in the load file. Corresponds directly to a software version in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display. alpha 'A': alpha test beta 'B': beta test production null: normal, production software special 'S': special, custom software

loadFileSoftwareVersion.name: loadFileSoftwareVersion
loadFileSoftwareVersion.description: The software version of the image in the load file. Corresponds directly to a software version in the section labeled 'Load image files' in the MANAGER FILES display. For example, the version display for loadFileSoftwareVersionType 'production' and loadFileSoftwareVersion '2.2.0.0' is 'V2.2'. The version display for loadFileSoftwareVersionType 'beta' and loadFileSoftwareVersion '3.1.0.4' is 'V3.1B4'.

paramService.name: paramService
paramService.description: Control for allowing parameter storage service for any client. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER SERVICE and the value labeled 'Parameter Service:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

paramDefaultService.name: paramDefaultService
paramDefaultService.description: Control for allowing default parameter loading service for any client. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER DEFAULT SERVICE and the value labeled 'Parameter Default Service:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

paramDrive.name: paramDrive
paramDrive.description: Identification number of the disk drive where parameters are stored. Corresponds directly to PARAMETER DRIVE and the value labeled 'Parameter Drive:' in the MANAGER CHARACTERISTICS display.

paramActive.name: paramActive
paramActive.description: The number of params in progress. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Currently Paraming:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

paramStorageActive.name: paramStorageActive
paramStorageActive.description: The number of parameter storage operations in progress. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Currently saving parameters:' in the MANAGER STATUS display.

paramFileNumber.name: paramFileNumber
paramFileNumber.description: The number of parameter files currently stored. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'Parameter files' and 'files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileTable.name: paramFileTable
paramFileTable.description: A list of param file entries. The number of entries is given by paramFileNumber.

paramFileEntry.name: paramFileEntry
paramFileEntry.description: Parameter values for a param file entry.

paramFileIdentificationType.name: paramFileIdentificationType
paramFileIdentificationType.description: The type of identification value in paramFileIdentification. Corresponds indirectly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileIdentification.name: paramFileIdentification
paramFileIdentification.description: Identification of the param file, an Ethernet address, as indicated by paramFileIdentificationType. Corresponds indirectly to a file name part in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileEntryStatus.name: paramFileEntryStatus
paramFileEntryStatus.description: The status of the entry. Set to 'invalid' to remove the entry, which corresponds indirectly to the PURGE MANAGER PARAMETER FILES command. Actual removal of the entry is implementation specific.

paramFileWrite.name: paramFileWrite
paramFileWrite.description: The time the parameter file was last written. Corresponds directly to a date and time in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileSize.name: paramFileSize
paramFileSize.description: The number of bytes stored in the param file. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'bytes' in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.

paramFileParameterVersion.name: paramFileParameterVersion
paramFileParameterVersion.description: The version number of the parameter data in the file. Corresponds directly to the value labeled 'ver' in the section labeled 'Parameter files' in the MANAGER FILES display.
